⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of 'California'
node WIZ · WIZ · ⟦'California':WIZ:400435⟧

WHO   — 'California' — the word, the destination, the grief
WHAT  — The coded grief: the one thing he can still say, standing in for everything he can't — where his sister was happy, where the loss must be carried.
WHERE — WIZ · The Wizard (1989)  Framework inputs: The Wizard (1989, dir. Todd Holland, Universal); verified cast & Nintendo history  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's emotional engine is a word that means a place that means a sister — the destination is the mourning.
HOW   — By repetition until it becomes a compass: say 'California' enough and it points the whole family west.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  One word for a place, a sister, and a goodbye he can't otherwise speak.

